# The hook-script templates are executed by an interpreter that does not
# tolerate the wrong line endings: cmd.exe parses a `.cmd` up to each CR (an
# LF-only file makes it run fragments of the comment block as commands), and a
# CRLF `.sh` makes the kernel look for an interpreter named `sh\r`. Pin both so
# a checkout under any `core.autocrlf` setting stores the right bytes.
#
# `renderHookScript` normalizes line endings again when it materializes a
# script, so a mangled checkout still produces a working hook — this file keeps
# the source of truth honest rather than being the only line of defense.
*.cmd text eol=crlf
*.sh  text eol=lf
